article.description: — Charles Bassey had 21 points as Western Kentucky rolled past Rice 89-66 on Saturday.
article.headline: Bassey scores 21 to carry Western Kentucky past Rice 89-66
article.linkText: Bassey scores 21 to carry Western Kentucky past Rice 89-66
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ky. -- — Charles Bassey had 21 points as Western Kentucky rolled past Rice 89-66 on Saturday. Bassey shot 9 for 10 from the field. Taveion Hollingsworth had 16 points and seven assists for Western Kentucky (15-4, 8-2 Conference USA), which earned its sixth consecutive victory. Luke Frampton added 15 points. Carson Williams had 14 points, seven rebounds and three blocks. Western Kentucky posted a season-high 24 assists. Quincy Olivari had 14 points for the Owls (12-10, 6-8). Cavit Ege Havsa added 12 points and seven rebounds. Cameron Sheffield had 11 points. The Hilltoppers improve to 2-0 against the Owls for the season. Western Kentucky defeated Rice 77-71 on Friday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
